text: UK is 7-9 on layups and 3-3 on dunks so far in the game.
Here’s your stats from the first half. pic.twitter.com/ePGYkol18F
End of 1H | UK 52, Centre 24.
Killeya-Jones has pulled down the last three rebounds for UK, and Gabriel makes his second three to put the Cats up 24.
Diallo checks in for Washington.
After the last putback by Killeya-Jones, every Wildcat in the game so far has made a shot from the floor.
Washington becomes UK's first double-digit scorer of the night after he knocks down a free throw to give him 10.
3:17 1H | UK 42, Centre 24. Washington with 9, Green with 8 as the Cats are on a 14-2 run in the last 4:43.
Knox checks in for Diallo as UK gets a delay of game warning. CAts currently on a 10-0 run.
Diallo misses his free throw, but Richards gets the board and throws it down hard.
Knox gets his first points of the game with 7:32 left in the first half on a layup that puts UK up 10.
Another three from the Colonels, and UK is up 28-22.
After a pair of free throws, Centre trims UK's lead to 9.
Gilgeous-Alexander in the game for Diallo as the Cats take a 25-10 lead.
Against Centre, the Cats are shooting 70% from the field, 75% from deep and 75% from the free throw line.
Green knocks down his second three of the game on his second attempt.
Quade Green checks in for Gilgeous-Alexander and Sacha Killeya-Jones is in for Gabriel.
Washington gets a putback dunk to give him six points and the Cats a 19-6 lead.
Washington back in for Knox.
Gilgeous-Alexander tips a pass, then gets a quick block and rebound to shut down the Colonels' possession.
Diallo checks into the game for Washington.
Washington puts Centre's Spitzer on a poster to give the Cats a seven point lead.
Washington takes a hard foul driving to the basket, drawing some boos from the crowd. He hits both free throws and the Cats lead 7-2.
Green opens the game with a three-pointer to give UK the first lead.
The Cats win the tip, and we're under way at Rupp Arena.
UK’s starters against Centre College: Quade Green, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, Kevin Knox, PJ Washington and Wenyen Gabriel.

Snell praised Gran for his play calling, getting him to the outside.
Benny Snell Jr.: We came out with a little more ambition, a little more drive.""
Johnson said Richardson has been consistent all year and works hard to be the best player on the field.
Johnson said he's a winner because he's not a quitter"."
Johnson said he didn't run out of the tunnel fast enough to start the next drive after his injury.
Johnson said building trust has been an integral part of his good choices on reads.
Stephen Johnson said it took a couple days" to come back from the injury, still isn't 100%."
Schlarman said the guys did a good job blocking in space.
Schlarman said Jackson put the offense in a good position with his good calls.
John Schlarman: I definitely thought we played with more continuity.""
Jackson said he's building chemistry with the first practice team on the front line.
Jackson on last-minute viewing of defenses: It's like studying right before a final.""
Drake Jackson said Stoops challenged the offense and said it kept them determined to move the ball.
Richardson said he knew the team was going to win when Stephen Johnson came back onto the field in the third.
Richardson on his big catch against Tennessee: I knew my toe was in.""
Lynn Bowden Jr. said throwing the ball isn't that much different in college than it was for him in high school.
Gran said Tavin Richardson has been the most consistent guy out there"."
Gran said Ole Miss's tackles are really, really good.""
Gran said the team had conversations about the ball security on the sideline and every day in practice.
Gran said CJ Conrad had his best game of the season, despite not catching a ball.
Gran said some of the problems they created for Tennessee's defense were due to previously known plays in different formations.
Gran said a few players were banged up, including Stephen Johnson. He'll be ready to play Saturday, according to Gran.

FINAL | UK 92, MSU 67 Diallo: 23 points, 1 rebound, 1 assist.
Green gets fouled on a layup attempt with 11 seconds remaining and hits the free throws to put the Cats up 92-67.
Diallo throws down a breakaway dunk to put the Cats up 23 with 30 seconds left.
Green hits the layup with contact and then the free throw to put UK up 19 with 3:24 left.
Tonight’s attendance is 14,138.
Diallo nails his second three of the game to put the Cats up 19 with 4:15 to play.
Cats force Morehead's 22nd turnover by forcing a 5-second violation.
Djimon Henson clutching his face after a missed rebound, play is stopped to check on him.
Diallo gets a dunk of his own as Morehead's Harris gets out of the way for a 14-point UK lead.
Gilgeous-Alexander becomes the leading scorer for the Cats as a layup gives him 17.
As Thompson fouls Diallo, two Eagles have four fouls and four more have three.
Killeya-Jones checking in for Washington now.
Cats up 68-54 with 7:25 left in the game after Washington's free throws.
A three by Morehead ends their three-and-a-half minute scoring drought.
Knox throws down a two-handed alley-oop and swings from the rim to put the cats up 15.
Green knocks down his first three-pointer of the contest to put the cats up 13.
Gilgeous-Alexander pulls down a rebound while getting fouled to send him to the line. He makes one, and the Cats are up 10 with 9:04 left.
Cats score four straight after Gilgeous-Alexander hits a layup and Washington dunks after a steal. Cats up nine.
Gabriel swats one off the glass, but the Cats can't rebound and Morehead puts it back in. Cats lead 54-51 with 11:31 left.
Diallo makes the free throw, and the Cats are up five with 12:20 left.
Another three for the Eagles cuts the UK lead to two, Diallo responds with a basket plus the foul.
Knox drives into the open lane for a one-handed tomahawk to put the Cats up five.
Another three for the Eagles, Cats lead 49-46 with 14:00 left.
UK now in the bonus with 14:26 left in the half as Gilgeous-Alexander knocks down a pair of free throws.
Cooper knocks down a three to bring the Eagles to within four.
Diallo becoming UK's third double-digit scorer after knocking down two free throws. He has 11.
Harris has taken the last three shots for Morehead, and just made two free throws to cut the UK lead to seven.
Tai Wynyard checking in for the first time in the game, replacing Richards after he turns it over.
Kevin Knox responds with an and-one contested dunk. Cats up eight.
Cats get caught flat-footed as Chatman gets the and-one bucket to bring Morehead within six.
Gabriel with the second big block of the game for the Cats, swatting one to the perimeter.
The first point of the half goes to Gilgeous-Alexander, who makes one of his free throws after getting fouled shooting.
The Cats will begin the half with Gabriel, Gilgeous-Alexander, Knox, Richards and Green on the floor.
Green, Knox and Gilgeous-Alexander lead all players in steals with three, two and two, respectively.
Morehead State committed 17 turnovers in the first half while taking 18 shots.
Every player that has checked in for the Cats so far except for Richards has at least one point.
Stats from the first half. pic.twitter.com/kmZBitlGYG
Halftime | UK 39 Morehead State 28.
Timeout called by Morehead State with 29 seconds remaining in the half, UK leads 39-25.
After his and-one free throw, Knox becomes the first Cat with 10 points.
Washington with three fouls, gets replaced by Richards. 1:22 1H
Morehead State is out rebounding UK 12-9.
3:59 1H | UK leads 32-20. Diallo, Green and Knox have scored 24 of UK’s points.
Emanuael Thompson with a contested dunk over Gilgeous-Alexander. Gets the Morehead State supports on their feet.
P.J. Washington recovering from a UK turnover with a heavy block into the stands.
Quade Green now up to eight points. 3-4 from the court.
Cats then go on a 7-0 run to build their lead nine. Free throws coming from Green when we return from a timeout. 7:38 1H.
Djimon Henson of Morehead hits a three, trimming UK’s lead to two.
11:34 1H | UK 16 Morehead State 11.
Sacha Killeya-Jones checks in for the first time tonight, replaces Quade Green.
UK had missed their last four shots before Gilgeous-Alexander hit that midrange jumper.
Timeout on the floor, 15:52 1H | U 10 Morehead State 5. Cats are 4-9 to start. Diallo and Knox both with five points.
Gilgeous-Alexander gets swatted at the rim, but on the next play Diallo nails a three. 10-5 UK.
Washington wins the tip and we are underway.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, Hamidou Diallo, Kevin Knox, PJ Washington and Wenyen Gabriel are the starters for tonight’s game.

Final: UK 70 Albany 46. Cats go undefeated in the Kentucky Classic behind a big day from Akhator.
Now Lashae Halsel checks into the game for the first time in her college career, less than a minute remaining, Cats in full control.
Paige Poffenberger checks into the game for her first time in her college career.
Akhator uses her strength to create space in the paint and score her 27th and 28th points of the game
Rice with some good fast break defense to prevent the Danes from scoring, Cats ball.
Epps gets her first field goal of the game with a fast break layup, Cats lead 66-39.
Cats lead by 24, their largest lead of the game, so far.
Tiani-Jo Carter of the Danes able to walk over to the bench with the help of teammates and trainers.
Albany player down after taking some contact in the paint
Epps back in the game at the start of the fourth quarter.
End of the 3rd: UK 53 Albany 34. Akhator with 22 points, 13 rebounds. She is the only player with double-digit points and rebounds.
Another Akhator three-point play after getting fouled in the paint, and hitting the and-one free throw. Cats have their largest lead at 19.
Akhator blocks a three-point attempt by the Danes, Danes get the rebound but step out of bounds, Cats ball
Epps can be seen riding the stationary bike on the bench, probably trying to loosen up the tendinitis she reported yesterday.
Neither team has scored a field goal in almost three minutes, the Cats are field goal-less for the last 4:13.
Epps get her first points of the night, hits two free throws to extend the Cats’ lead to 45-27.
The Danes’ leading returning scorer, Imani Tate, shooting 3-16 from the court.
Akhator grabs her 10th rebound to give her a double-double before the five minute mark in the third quarter.
Akhator hits two free throws to extend the Cats’ lead to 17.
Cann knocks down her first three of night, Cann now with eight points.
Akhator back in the game
Early sub as Cann replaces Akhator, Cann grabs a rebound within 15 seconds of coming in the game
Second half underway at Memorial Coliseum, starters on the court for the Cats
That zone defense the Cats have installed is working, they held the Danes to 22% shooting on the half.
Akhator leads all scorers with 15 points, only three rebounds away from another double-double.
The Cats close the half on a 9-0 run to increase their lead to 36-19 at halftime. Cats also held the Danes scoreless the final five minutes
Morris knocks down her second triple of the game to extend the Cats’ lead to 15, 1:38 left in the half. Timeout called by Albany
Akhator swats a shot back to the Kentucky bench. Akhator second block of the game.
Timeout called, Cats lead 27-19. 4:46 left in the half.
Epps with her third assist, this time passing it to Cann who put in the layup
Epps with a beautiful pass to the post, where Akhator was open for the easy layup.
Still scoreless in the second quarter, but Murray is heading to the line for two free throws.
The Cats held the Danes to 24% shooting in that first quarter.
End of the 1st: UK 19 Albany 11. Akhator leads all scorers with nine points, also has four rebounds.
Danes are scoreless in the last five minutes of play.
Jessica Hardin makes a three and gets fouled, but unable to make the free throw to complete the four-point play. Cats lead 17-7
Akhator and Epps back in the game for he Cats following the timeout
Timeout called, UK leads Albany 14-7. The Cats currently on a 9-0
Cann knocks down all three free throws to give the Cats an 14-7 lead, 5:17 left in the first.
Cann is fouled behind the three-point line and is due for three free throws
Makenzie Cann and Jaida Roper are the first subs off the bench, they replace Epps and Akhator
Akhator has scored the first seven points for the Cats off of 3-4 shooting.
First points from the Cats come from an Akhator and-one. Akhator hits the free throw to give the Cats an early 3-2 lead.
We are underway at Memorial Coliseum where the Cats are taking on the Albany Great Danes, the Cats win the tip.
Tipoff just about 30 minutes away
Starting lineup for tonight’s UK women’s basketball game: G: Makayla Epps G: Taylor Murray G: Maci Morris F: Evelyn Akhator C: Alyssa Rice
